definition: to deliver/to carry/to give (as a present)/to present (with)/to see off/to send
to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]

sentences.english: The summons was served upon the defendant.

sentences.english: We delivered the merchandise to them.
sentences.chinese: 我們把貨物送交給他們。

sentences.english: If a man breaks the law, it is everyone's duty to hand him over to justice.
sentences.chinese: 假如有人犯了法，人人有責把他送交法庭審判。

definition: to pass on to sb/to carry and give to sb else
to report to one's superiors/to appear in the news/to reply to a letter
receipt (written acknowledgement of receipt of an item)
in custody/to keep sb in detention
to transfer (a case, a person, files etc)
to hand over to/to give to higher authority/to seek connections in high places
(formal) to inform by letter/to submit in writing
